article.headline: Murray State 69, Austin Peay 68 (OT)
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Trey Pearson tipped in a missed shot in overtime and led with 14 points to scratch out a 69-68 win for Murray State against Austin Peay Thursday night. Murray State (15-5, 12-2 Ohio Valley Conference) and Austin Peay (12-11, 7-7) went back and forth the whole game, with eight lead changes in the first half and 12 in the second. From a 39-38 edge for the Governors at the half, both teams stuttered from the line. The Governors went 13-of-17 from the line in the first half, but dropped to 1-and-4 in the second and overtime. The Racers were 1-3 from the line in the second, which included Justin Orr's shot with 1:53 left to tie it at 60 and force overtime. With only five seconds left, Pearson tipped in a missed 3-point attempt by Shawn Witherspoon for the win. No other Racers were in double digits, but Darnell Hopkins and Issian Redding each had 9 points. Zac Schlader led the Governors with 14, followed by Drake Reed with 10 and Maurice Hampton with 9.
